unittitle_ssm: James and Karla Murray Counter Culture exhibition photographs
abstract_ssm: The collection comprises 41 color photographic prints, taken between the late 1990s and 2008. There are 25 11" x 14" prints and 16 panoramic photographs of various sizes. The photographs depict storefronts in Brooklyn. The photographs were part of an exhibition at Brooklyn Historical Society in 2008 titled Counter Culture: The Disappearing Face of Brooklyn's Storefronts.
